DataElement.definition: Text designations that identify gender. Gender is described as the assemblage of properties that distinguish people on the basis of their societal roles. [Explanatory Comment 1: Identification of gender is based upon self-report and may come from a form, questionnaire, interview, etc.]
DataElement.origin: NCISTD: NCI CRF Harmonization and Standards Initiative
DataElement.changeDescription: 3/1/22 jk Designated, added CDS alt name and CSI. 1/21/20 jk removed from MCL Biospecimen CSI.  1/29/19 jk MCL CSI and  AQT added.  7/17/18 jk revised MCL Core CSI mapping. 05/25/2016 wz added NWU CS/CSI.5/18/16 jk moved from EDRN to MCL context CSI.   Replaces v2.0 with a Value Domain that has shortened permissible values of 'Male' and 'Female'. 4/4/2012 dmr: two values that were erroneously added perhaps during a model load were removed (Female Gender and Male Gender) without a version change, since these two values were not part of the vetted value set.
DataElement.administrativeNotes: 9/14/23 Added CCDI alts and CSI. mr

DataElementConcept.definition: A person's gender which is based on the assemblage of properties that distinguish people on the basis of their societal roles.
DataElementConcept.origin: OMB/NCI:Office of Management and Budget/National Cancer Institute
DataElementConcept.changeDescription: Update to use the caBIG Property dbw

Property.definition: Gender is the assemblage of properties that distinguish people on the basis of their societal roles.

Concepts.definition: Characteristics of people that are socially constructed, including norms, behaviors, and roles based on sex. As a social construct, gender varies from society to society and can change over time. (Adapted from WHO.) IMPORTANT NOTICE: The NCI Thesaurus contains biomedical terminologies that NCI does not own or control. This concept contains gender-related content that does not comply with Executive Order 14168.

ValueDomain.changeDescription: Working with EVS to Updated Permissible Values to Reflect requested terms in "Representation of Sex and Gender 06202005.doc. Replaces v1.0 with shortened permissible values of 'Female' and 'Male'. Replaces v2.0 with a Value Domain that has shortened permissible values of 'Male' and 'Female'. 4/4/2012/dmr: two values that were erroneously added perhaps during a model load were removed (Female Gender and Male Gender) without a version change, since these two values were not part of the vetted value set.
